        ";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";s:5:"child";a:3:{s:0:"";a:6:{s:5:"title";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:50:"The Pope brings his message in English and Spanish";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"link";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:130:"http://www.chicagonow.com/chicanisima-latino-politics-news-and-culture/2015/09/the-pope-brings-his-message-in-english-and-spanish/";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:8:"comments";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:139:"http://www.chicagonow.com/chicanisima-latino-politics-news-and-culture/2015/09/the-pope-brings-his-message-in-english-and-spanish/#comments";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:7:"pubDate";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:31:"Wed, 23 Sep 2015 09:05:44 -0600";s:7:"attribs";a:0:{}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:4:"guid";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:78:"http://www.chicagonow.com/chicanisima-latino-politics-news-and-culture/?p=3299";s:7:"attribs";a:1:{s:0:"";a:1:{s:11:"isPermaLink";s:5:"false";}}s:8:"xml_base";s:0:"";s:17:"xml_base_explicit";b:0;s:8:"xml_lang";s:0:"";}}s:11:"description";a:1:{i:0;a:5:{s:4:"data";s:1950:"At the White House, Pope Francis began his speech Wednesday morning by paying respect to immigrants.

"As the son of an immigrant family, I am happy to be a guest in this country, which was largely built by such families," he said.

The Pope reminded us to fight injustice, discrimination and to protect the vulnerable.

He delivered his remarks in English but also expect to hear him speak a lot of Spanish while here in the U.S.

Below please find my opinion column on the topic syndicated by the <a href="http://www.progressivemediaproject.org/" target="_blank">Progressive Media Project</a>.
<blockquote>
<p style="text-align: left;">During Pope Francis' travels in the United States, his public appearances will be a rebuke to the English-only crowd.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Most of his speeches and Masses will be in Spanish, and there is nothing wrong with the pope or anybody else speaking in another language in this country.</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">English is not the official language of the United States. However, there have always been politicians who've used English as a political issue.</p>
